Overall black. Pronotal disc (Figs 
9F, H
, 
10
) entirely pink or orangish, sometimes as two almost contiguous spots occupying most disc, pronotal expansions from entirely black to entirely testaceous, mildly translucent anteriorly. Elytron (Fig. 
9A, C
) black, with a pale-yellow longitudinal stripe about 4/5
x
as long as elytra. Legs (Fig. 
9B, D
) dark brown to black, except for trochanters, which are brown. Sternum VIII entirely dark brown, without lateral vitreous spots. Pygidium (Fig. 
9H
) entirely dark brown.

